Spike Protein Functional Summary

- S1 subunit: Binds to host cell receptors (primarily ACE2) to mediate viral attachment. Can also use alternative receptors (e.g., NRP1/NRP2, integrins, ASGR1) and trigger either membrane fusion or endocytosis depending on cleavage state.

- S2 subunit: Drives membrane fusion after activation. Undergoes major conformational changes to fuse viral and host membranes, enabling entry of viral RNA into the host cell.

- S2' subunit: Activated by host protease cleavage (e.g., TMPRSS2 or cathepsins), exposing the fusion peptide and initiating irreversible membrane fusion.
